Israeli Stocks: Brainsway, Pluristem Therapeutics Were Active

-- B y   R o n i t   G o o d m a n
-- 
2011-03-01T15:27:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/israeli-stocks-brainsway-elbit-systems-israel-petrochemical.html
  Israel ’s TA-25 Index declined the
most since Feb. 24, retreating 1.2 percent to 1,273.67 at the
4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv. Investors traded about 2 billion
shekels ($551 million) in shares and convertible securities.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Brainsway Ltd. (BRIN IT) increased to the highest level in
almost a week, adding 2.1 percent to 8.814 shekels. The
developer of devices for neurological disorders said tests using
its Deep TMS device with H Coil was safe and improved motor
functionality in Parkinson’s patients.    Pluristem Therapeutics Inc . (PSTI IT) climbed the most in
more than a month, jumping 6.5 percent to 9.63 shekels. A
preclinical study showed local administration of the company’s
cell therapy following muscle injury resulted in “significant
improvement” in the recovery of muscle function compared with
the control group.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ronit Goodman in  Tel Aviv  at 
